The ACE family is in no way a good influence on kids, which makes up like 90% of their audience

textDisplay:
Is there a video on how creators use thumbnails as clickbait as in the case of the Ace family? 

I kinda feel like I did it before in a title out of desperation, it was about my art lmao I titled it 'A Compelling Inside Look To The Thought Process Of An Artist | Free Shipping!'. I just wanted somebody to buy my art lmao and free shipping is a pretty cool incentive, I thought. 

Sometimes, in retrospect, my vlogs make me cringe but I keep them up as a reminder of how far I've come. I also don't think erasing everything is a viable solution because I have to love all of me, even cringy me, and learn from those moments.

In the end I've learned that you shouldn't act out of desperation because you lower your worth thinking you'll get what you want but you don't so.... just not worth it. And that goes for relationships too.

Stop being relatable. Start being interesting.

I sat next to Jerry Seinfeld and his wife at an off-off-Broadway play a couple of years ago. They came in 20 minutes into the show. It's a very small theater so they disrupted everyone. She wore a glitter dress that reflected all the stage lights in the tiny theater. During the intermission, a woman walked up to them (they were seated on the isle), and before she even had a chance to speak, Jerry said "no pictures or autographs"
She was one of the ushers who came over to ask that his Mrs. wear her coat during the next act because the sparkly glare coming off her outfit was distracting to the audience 
Again, this was a tiny off-off-Broadway show attended by real New Yorkers ... not one person came up to him
